      <h2>ROI Methodology: The Gold Standard for Franchise Valuation</h2>
      <p>The <strong>Return on Investment (ROI)</strong> method is the most widely accepted approach for valuing franchises. ROI represents the total financial return a franchise owner derives from their investment.</p>

      <h3>How ROI is Calculated:</h3>
      <div class="calculation-box">
        <h4>ROI Formula:</h4>
        <p><strong>ROI = (Net Profit รท Total Investment) ร 100</strong></p>
      </div>

      <h3>Key Components of Franchise ROI:</h3>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Net Income:</strong> Annual profit after all expenses</li>
        <li><strong>Owner's Salary:</strong> Compensation taken by the franchise owner</li>
        <li><strong>Initial Investment:</strong> Franchise fee + startup costs + working capital</li>
        <li><strong>Cash Flow:</strong> Operating cash generated by the business</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

